         The Department of Evaluation & Decision Science at Mercy Virtual is seeking a Senior Data Scientist to work within a team of other advanced scientists in the generation, extraction, and compilation of data to perform creative, high-quality, state-of-the-art analyses and evaluations that answer questions, make discoveries, and support decision-making within the emerging virtual healthcare segment. Mercy has an incredible amount of operational, clinical, and financial data and increasing capacity to integrate additional data from external and device sources, such as geospatial indexes and biosensors. This is a great opportunity to work on the forefront of technology and methodology to address challenging health care questions and uncover the keys to the successful delivery of virtual healthcare services. The candidate should have an affinity for learning and a growth mindset, be able to effectively develop, document, and communicate project plans, demonstrate expertise with data analytic functions and related software tools, and deliver outputs on a tight time budget. This position will report to the Director of the Department of Evaluation & Decision Science.
          Responsibilities:
          Proven ability to build and manage successful relationships with internal and external stakeholders and work both independently and within a team-centric environment
          Effectively communicate with internal and external stakeholders to develop requirements, document data definitions, select appropriate data sources, extract, integrate, visualize, and analyze data using appropriate data mining and data analysis tools e.g. SQL, R, SAS, Python, etc
          Integrate decentralized data systems, devise/implement strategies for the development of data marts and data warehouses, and work with the Mercy Virtual team members on data commercialization opportunities
          Develop data commercialization and publication quality data sets and analyses utilizing data from various internal and external sources in collaboration with internal and external business partners
          Perform duties and responsibilities in a manner consistent with our Mission, Values, and Charism
          Perform other duties as assigned
         Qualifications:
          Because you’re committed to excellence, you understand the importance of being properly prepared for your role at Mercy. That’s why you’ll bring to your role the right set of qualifications:
          Required Qualifications
         :
          Graduate degree in Computer Science, Statistics, Mathematics, Data Science, or similar field
          Have at least 5 years of experience in a similar role
          Possess a working knowledge of descriptive and inferential statistics, causal process assessment, data mining, and predictive modeling
          Display understanding of study design, validation, and scientific standards for communication of health care data in the US
          Display understanding of and ability to use programming languages and related applications (e.g., SQL, R, SAS, and/or Python)
          Experience with Business Intelligence tools, such as SAP Business Objects, Qlikview, or SAS Visual Analytics
          Show ability to comprehend and apply data relationships across multiple sources and domains
          Demonstrate capacity to build large, complex datasets
          Utilize analytical skills to critically evaluate information gathered from multiple sources, reconcile conflicts, decompose high-level information into details, and abstract up from low-level information to a more general understanding
          Have proven, practical problem-solving skills and demonstrated experience presenting information and data visualization to technical and non-technical audiences in a clear and compelling manner that inspires action
          Possess strong organizational skills, an orientation toward detail, and be a team player
          Work under pressure and meet deadlines
          Preferred Qualifications (required qualifications plus):
          Doctoral degree in Computer Science, Statistics, Mathematics, Data Science, or similar field
          Understanding of and experience with Big Data tools (e.g., Hadoop, SAP Hana, NoSQL)
          Clarity Certification
